description:
Senior Manager (Communications and News / Digital Specialist / Marketing and Events) (at the rank of Administrative Assistant I) and Manager (Marketing and Events) (at the rank of Administrative Assistant II) in the Communications and Public Affairs Office of the Registry (Ref.: 511288) 

The Communications and Public Affairs Office (CPAO) of the Registry of the University of Hong Kong (HKU) strengthens the reputation of University through a range of strategies including media relations and digital communications.  The Office is also responsible for University events and ceremonies, publications, both external and internal communications, crisis management and community engagement.  CPAO is currently elevating and expanding its scope of services. We are looking for talented candidates to join the team.

The key responsibilities of the Senior Manager (Communications and News / Digital Specialist) of CPAO are to:

support the Director and the Assistant Director in engaging and building rapport with both local and international media; create multimedia content, conduct interviews and write-ups;
handle media enquiries, draft and edit media releases, organise media events, press conferences and media interviews;
help develop a digital portal and take up the role as the Editor; and
coordinate the University’s websites revamp and liaise with users and stakeholders on the sitemap, navigation and design etc.

The key responsibilities of the Senior Manager / Manager (Marketing and Events) are to:

support the Director and the Assistant Director in the development and execution of effective corporate marketing, branding and community engagement plans;
coordinate the University branding exercise;
organise University ceremonies, including Congregation, inaugural lectures, awards presentations, visits, and others;
manage the official online and print publications of the University; and
implement marketing and community engagement programmes.

For the above posts, we expect the applicants to have:

a good bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline;
at least eight years’ relevant experience, with at least three years in a managerial position for consideration of appointment as Senior Manager; or at least five years’ relevant experience, with at least two years in a supervisory position for consideration of appointment as Manager;
the ability to manage fast-moving projects and collaborate with internal and external cross-functional teams in a complicated environment;
experience in Higher Education as a plus;
a good command of English and Chinese;
an excellent command of web technologies, social media platform trends, data analytics for marketing; and
a willingness to work outside regular work hours and on duty roster.

The appointment will be made from as soon as possible, on a three-year fixed-term basis for the Senior Manager post and on a two-year fixed-term basis for the Manager post, with a possibility of renewal.

A highly competitive salary commensurate with qualifications and experience will be offered. The appointments carry leave and medical/dental benefits.  The appointment will attract a contract-end gratuity and University contribution to a retirement benefits scheme, totalling up to 15% of basic salary for Senior Manager post and up to 10% of basic salary for Manager post.

The University only accepts online application for the above posts.  Applicants should apply online at the University’s careers site (https://jobs.hku.hk) and upload an up-to-date C.V.  Review of application will commence as soon as possible and continue until February 16, 2022. 

The University is an equal opportunities employer
and is committed to equality, ethics, inclusivity, diversity and transparency

Job Responsibilities

Develop brand and marketing strategy for the core medical brand(s) and drive the implementation to enhance brand equity and increase market penetration;
Build relationship with medical professionals for brand growth opportunities, including awareness building, lead generation and partnership liaison;
Establish partnerships with local and global patient peer groups for brand growth opportunities, including patient community engagement;
Plan and manage B2B and B2C events, including participating or, if necessary, organizing conference, seminars, webinars;
Develop master sales & marketing communication assets and ensure proper adaptation and usage of the materials;
Work closely with media (esp. news outlets) and agencies for media plan development and execution, including social media, SEM, display ad, PR (including interviews and advertorials);
Lead content development for website and social platforms;
Develop CRM plan and enhance the existing membership loyalty program;
Partner with sales team to gain market insights and sharpen sales conversion tactics;
Liaise with universities for both regular marketing activities and long-term strategic partnership.

Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Science or Business; Pharmacy or Medical related discipline is a plus;
3 years of marketing experience in pharmaceutical industry; particularly in ethical channel is a plus;
Fluent in spoken and written English and Chinese;
Open-minded attitude and creativity to bring in new initiatives;
Strong branding mindset and strategic thinking for long-term brand development;
Strong desire to learn and ability to multi-task;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook).

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po, N.T.

