Job Summary:
Working closely with event sales teams in each market, the job holder will be responsible for overall management of Event Services team and deliver the highest quality service at Disney standard to various kinds of Business Solutions & Events (BS&E) events, including corporate events, wedding events, and social catering events.
Responsibilities:
Lead a team of Event Services professionals to manage and deliver various types of BS&E events that take place in the resort hotels and in Hong Kong Disneyland Park, and ensure the team consistently offer world-class level of service to drive client and guest satisfaction for each event;
Drive creation and capturing of upselling/ cross-selling opportunities during the course of event management and delivery with each client, and contribute to revenue generation under overall BS&E team;
Lead and support the team on problem solving and solution formulation during the event delivery process, when there are conflicts/ inconsistency among clients’ requests, standards/ requirement from internal stakeholders, available resources, government regulations, etc.;
Lead the team to maintain high standard of storage and upkeep for key reusable amenities and props for BS&E event formats, and/ or to request replenishment of consumable items when necessary, in close collaboration with different vendors and internal partners;
Drive knowledge management efforts among the team, to ensure all team members have the training and resources to carry out their current responsibilities and get ready for more, as well as continuous product, process, systems and operational knowledge refresh;
Continuously explore ways to streamline and improve event management and delivery processes, to improve work efficiency and quality;
Act as a primary internal point of contact for the team in terms of different operational issues, or cross-department projects/initiatives.
Basic Qualifications:
Bachelor degree or above;
At least 7 years of event management experience with a luxury hotel/ resort/ venue, with extensive knowledge in hospitality management, food & beverage and banquet catering operations.
Experience with operational teams within HKDL and/ or experience in handling sizable groups and events would be an advantage;
Demonstrated track-record and ability to lead a team;
Be able to work independently and under pressure, in an ever-changing business environment;
Excellent presentation, problem solving, negotiations and coaching skills;
Excellent written (English and Chinese) and verbal (English, Cantonese, Mandarin) communication skills.
